The Court of Appeal in Abuja has dismissed the appeal filed by the All Progressives Congress (APC) and its governorship candidate in Benue State, Emmauel Jime challenging the victory of Governor Samuel Ortom of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP at the polls. The appellate court’s panel, in a unanimous judgment delivered on Thursday by Justice Fred Oho, resolved all the issue in the appeal against the appellants. The appeal was dismissed for lacking in merit. The appellate court also awarded a fine of N150,000 against the appellants. Detail later… Appeal Court upholds Sanwo-Olu’s election A/Court reserves judgment in Akume, Jev's case, affirms Moro's victory Court of Appeal affirms Gov Obiano’s election